-- Peru Stocks: Aceros Arequipa, Alicorp, Candente, Pomalca
-- B y   N e y   H a y a s h i
-- 2012-05-11T17:43:59Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-11/peru-stocks-aceros-arequipa-alicorp-candente-pomalca.html
The following companies are having
unusual price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and share prices are as of 12:31 p.m. in  Lima .  The  Lima General Index (IGBVL)  slid 0.5 percent to 21,657.29. The
MSCI All Peru Capped Index lost 0.6 percent to 2,784.26.  Volcan Cia. Minera SAA (VOLCABC1 PE), Peru’s largest silver
and zinc producer, dropped 2.9 percent to 3.04 soles, the worst
performer on the Lima General Index, as silver declined in  New
York .  Candente Copper Corp. (DNT)  , a Canadian mining
exploration company with operations in Peru, declined 1.4
percent to 70 cents after copper fell in New York.  Cia. de Minas Buenaventura SAA  (BVN PE), the country’s
biggest precious-metals miner, retreated 1.7 percent to $38.25
as gold headed for its biggest weekly drop since March in New
York.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ney Hayashi in  Sao Paulo  at 
